{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":136045,"duration_api_ms":134485,"num_turns":13,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"b34e9402-4165-44f7-a4f4-8eb175e51024","total_cost_usd":1.20927195,"usage":{"input_tokens":14,"cache_creation_input_tokens":84987,"cache_read_input_tokens":1031339,"output_tokens":3097,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":84987,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":14,"outputTokens":3097,"cacheReadInputTokens":1031339,"cacheCreationInputTokens":84987,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.12433325,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":87,"outputTokens":4358,"cacheReadInputTokens":355342,"cacheCreationInputTokens":22022,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.0849387,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"evidence":["All 98 milestone_record tests pass (0 failures, 0 ignored) — verified by running cargo test --lib contexts::milestone_record","cargo clippy -- -D warnings passes cleanly (no warnings)","cargo fmt --all --check passes (no formatting issues)","Amendment fr-13-36f0aa72 FIXED: compare_task_run_recency (model.rs:379-381) now compares only started_at timestamps. latest_task_runs_per_bead (model.rs:386-406) uses `ordering != Ordering::Less` (line 394) so when started_at values are equal, later entries in the slice win. This means a running retry appended after a terminal entry with the same timestamp correctly outranks it, keeping the snapshot active.","Amendment fr-13-36f0aa72 model regression: latest_task_runs_per_bead_prefers_later_same_timestamp_retry_state (model.rs:877-915) seeds [Failed@T, Running@T] and verifies Running wins. Also collapse_task_run_attempts_preserves_same_timestamp_legacy_retries (model.rs:1013-1070) seeds 4 same-timestamp legacy rows and verifies 2 distinct collapsed attempts.","Amendment fr-13-36f0aa72 integration regression: same_timestamp_retry_keeps_snapshot_active (service.rs:1984-2059) runs start→fail→retry-at-same-T, asserts snapshot.status==Active, in_progress_beads==1, failed_beads==0, completed_beads==0 — confirming the running retry is correctly selected as the latest state.","Amendment fr-13-a74a46a6 FIXED: find_matching_running_task_run (model.rs:416-443) now ignores the _started_at parameter entirely. For run_id=None, line 438-439 matches any sole running entry `[entry] => Some(entry.clone())` regardless of timestamp, enabling recovery when the retry uses a different started_at.","Amendment fr-13-a74a46a6 model regression: find_matching_running_task_run_reuses_sole_runless_attempt_for_retry_repair (model.rs:944-971) seeds a Running entry at started_at=T, calls find_matching with started_at=T+30s and run_id=None, verifies it returns the existing entry.","Amendment fr-13-a74a46a6 integration regression: start_retry_without_run_id_repairs_partial_start_write (service.rs:2900-2970) uses FailFirstJournalAppend mock to simulate journal failure on first start. First start fails, leaving a Running lineage row. Retry with different started_at (now+5s) reuses the existing running row (runs remain 1), snapshot is valid with active_bead present.","model.rs: TaskRunEntry retains all required fields — milestone_id, bead_id, project_id, run_id, plan_hash, outcome, outcome_detail, started_at, finished_at — with serde(default, skip_serializing_if) for backward compatibility","service.rs: reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage (lines 163-226) uses latest_task_runs_per_bead to rebuild counters from canonical lineage, transitions Active→Ready when no active beads remain, preserves Paused status","service.rs: All mutation paths (update_status, persist_plan, record_bead_start, update_task_run) run under with_milestone_write_lock for serialized access","All prior acceptance criteria remain satisfied: milestone state answers 'what happened to bead X?', controller can update linkage after each run outcome, backward compatibility maintained"],"findings_or_gaps":["Both final-review amendments (fr-13-36f0aa72 and fr-13-a74a46a6) have been addressed with code changes and regression tests in completion round 14.","The _started_at parameter in find_matching_running_task_run is now entirely unused (prefixed with underscore). While this is functionally correct for the recovery path, it slightly widens the matching surface — a sole runless running entry will now be reused by ANY retry regardless of timestamp gap. This is acceptable because: (a) the function only runs on already-collapsed canonical task runs, (b) only a single open entry can exist per bead/project, and (c) the milestone mutation lock prevents concurrent creation of ambiguous state.","AppError::RunStartFailed is still used (service.rs ~line 555) for rejecting non-terminal outcomes in update_task_run, which is semantically a finalization rejection. A more specific error variant would be cleaner but this is cosmetic, not a correctness issue — carried forward from prior reviews.","The outstanding risk — milestone mutations span separate lineage, snapshot, and journal files without a cross-file transaction — remains. All paths are serialized by the milestone mutation lock and replay-safe, making this an acceptable trade-off for file-based storage.","Legacy attempts that still omit run_id remain inherently ambiguous for completion updates when multiple same-project attempts are open at once; this round improves single-open retry recovery but does not make multi-open legacy finalization deterministic."],"follow_up_or_amendments":[],"outcome":"approved"},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"d7a05faa-2286-40f1-baa2-03e48d008416"}
